 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🌍 Africa CDC Data Access\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to access public health surveillance data from the **African Centres for Disease Control and Prevention (Africa CDC)**.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "The Africa CDC coordinates disease surveillance and response across the African continent, covering:\n",
    "- **Disease outbreak surveillance**: Weekly outbreak briefs\n",
    "- **COVID-19 data**: Historical pandemic surveillance\n",
    "- **Event-Based Surveillance (EBS)**: Real-time threat detection\n",
    "- **Vaccination coverage**: Immunization program data\n",
    "- **Priority diseases**: Ebola, Marburg, Lassa fever, Cholera, Mpox, etc.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Website:** https://africacdc.org/\n",
    "\n",
    "**Coverage:** 55 African Union Member States"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📦 Setup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add scripts directory to path\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, str(Path.cwd().parent.parent / 'scripts'))\n",
    "\n",
    "from accessors.africa_cdc import AfricaCDCAccessor\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize accessor\n",
    "africa_cdc = AfricaCDCAccessor()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Africa CDC Accessor initialized successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🌍 African Union Member States\n",
    "\n",
    "Africa CDC covers all 55 African Union member states:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# List all countries\n",
    "countries = africa_cdc.list_countries()\n",
    "print(f\"Total AU member states: {len(countries)}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nFirst 15 countries:\")\n",
    "countries.head(15)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🗺️ Africa CDC Regions\n",
    "\n",
    "Africa CDC organizes countries into 5 geographical regions:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# View countries by region\n",
    "regions = africa_cdc.list_regions()\n",
    "\n",
    "for region in regions['region'].unique():\n",
    "    region_countries = regions[regions['region'] == region]\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n📍 {region} Region ({len(region_countries)} countries):\")\n",
    "    country_names = region_countries['country_name'].tolist()\n",
    "    print(\"  \" + \", \".join(country_names[:8]))\n",
    "    if len(country_names) > 8:\n",
    "        print(f\"  ... and {len(country_names) - 8} more\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🦠 Priority Diseases\n",
    "\n",
    "Africa CDC tracks priority diseases for the continent:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# List priority diseases\n",
    "diseases = africa_cdc.list_priority_diseases()\n",
    "print(f\"Total priority diseases: {len(diseases)}\\n\")\n",
    "diseases"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Categorize diseases by type\n",
    "hemorrhagic_fevers = ['EBOLA', 'MARBRG', 'LASSA', 'CCHF']\n",
    "vbd = ['DENGUE', 'MALARIA', 'YELLOW_FEVER', 'RVF']  # Vector-borne\n",
    "vaccine_preventable = ['MEASLES', 'MENINGITIS', 'INFLUENZA', 'YELLOW_FEVER']\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"🩸 Viral Hemorrhagic Fevers:\")\n",
    "for d in hemorrhagic_fevers:\n",
    "    print(f\"  - {d}: {africa_cdc.PRIORITY_DISEASES[d]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n🦟 Vector-Borne Diseases:\")\n",
    "for d in vbd:\n",
    "    print(f\"  - {d}: {africa_cdc.PRIORITY_DISEASES[d]}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n💉 Vaccine-Preventable Diseases:\")\n",
    "for d in vaccine_preventable:\n",
    "    print(f\"  - {d}: {africa_cdc.PRIORITY_DISEASES[d]}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Disease Outbreak Surveillance\n",
    "\n",
    "Access current and historical disease outbreak data:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get outbreak data for Ebola\n",
    "ebola_outbreaks = africa_cdc.get_disease_outbreaks(disease='EBOLA')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Ebola outbreak records: {len(ebola_outbreaks)}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nSample structure:\")\n",
    "ebola_outbreaks.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get outbreaks in East Africa\n",
    "east_africa = africa_cdc.get_countries_by_region('Eastern')\n",
    "print(f\"East African countries: {len(east_africa)}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "east_africa_outbreaks = africa_cdc.get_disease_outbreaks(\n",
    "    countries=east_africa[:10]  # First 10 for demo\n",
    ")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nOutbreak records for East Africa sample: {len(east_africa_outbreaks)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🦠 COVID-19 Historical Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Access COVID-19 surveillance data for African countries:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get COVID-19 data for selected countries\n",
    "covid_data = africa_cdc.get_covid_data(\n",
    "    countries=['ZA', 'NG', 'ET', 'KE', 'GH'],  # 5 major economies\n",
    "    date_range=('2020-03-01', '2021-12-31')\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"COVID-19 records: {len(covid_data)}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nCountries included:\")\n",
    "covid_data[['country_code', 'country_name']].drop_duplicates()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 💉 Vaccination Coverage\n",
    "\n",
    "Access vaccination coverage data:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get vaccination data for selected countries\n",
    "vax_data = africa_cdc.get_vaccination_coverage(\n",
    "    countries=['NG', 'ET', 'ZA', 'KE'],\n",
    "    vaccines=['COVID-19', 'Measles']\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Vaccination records: {len(vax_data)}\")\n",
    "vax_data.head(10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🚨 Event-Based Surveillance (EBS)\n",
    "\n",
    "Access real-time event-based surveillance alerts:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get EBS alerts for Sahel region\n",
    "sahel_countries = ['ML', 'NE', 'TD', 'BF', 'MR']\n",
    "\n",
    "ebs_alerts = africa_cdc.get_event_based_surveillance(\n",
    "    countries=sahel_countries,\n",
    "    date_range=('2024-01-01', '2024-12-31')\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"EBS alerts for Sahel: {len(ebs_alerts)}\")\n",
    "ebs_alerts.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📋 Weekly Outbreak Briefs\n",
    "\n",
    "Africa CDC publishes weekly outbreak briefs:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get outbreak briefs for a year\n",
    "briefs_2024 = africa_cdc.get_weekly_outbreak_brief(year=2024)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Total briefs in 2024: {len(briefs_2024)}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nFirst 5 weeks:\")\n",
    "briefs_2024.head()[['year', 'week', 'data_source']]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get specific week\n",
    "week_30 = africa_cdc.get_weekly_outbreak_brief(year=2024, week=30)\n",
    "print(\"Week 30 brief:\")\n",
    "week_30[['year', 'week', 'diseases_covered']]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📈 Regional Comparison\n",
    "\n",
    "Compare disease occurrence across regions:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Compare COVID-19 across regions\n",
    "regional_comparison = africa_cdc.compare_regions(\n",
    "    disease='COVID-19',\n",
    "    year=2021\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Regional comparison structure:\")\n",
    "regional_comparison if not regional_comparison.empty else \"No data available\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 📊 Country Summary\n",
    "\n    "Get outbreak summary by country:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get summary for all diseases\n",
    "summary_2024 = africa_cdc.get_summary_by_country(year=2024)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Summary records: {len(summary_2024)}\")\n",
    "summary_2024.head(10) if not summary_2024.empty else \"No data available\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 🔍 Data Access Notes\n",
    "\n",
    "### Current Implementation\n",
    "\n",
    "This accessor provides:\n",
    "- ✅ Complete metadata (55 AU member states, 5 regions)\n",
    "- ✅ Priority disease definitions\n",
    "- ✅ Structured data access methods\n",
    "- ✅ Regional and temporal filtering\n",
    "- ✅ Ready-to-use data structures\n",
    "\n",
    "### Future Enhancements\n",
    "\n",
    "For full data access, integrate with:\n",
    "1. **Africa CDC Weekly Briefs API** - Direct PDF parsing\n",
    "2. **IDSR databases** - National surveillance systems\n",
    "3. **EBS Platform** - Real-time event surveillance\n",
    "4. **WHO Immunization Data Portal** - Vaccination coverage\n",
    "\n",
    "### Data Availability\n",
    "\n",
    "| Data Type | Frequency | Access Method |\n",
    "|-----------|-----------|---------------|\n",
    "| Weekly outbreak briefs | Weekly | PDF downloads |\n",
    "| COVID-19 data | Daily (historical) | Africa CDC dashboard |\n",
    "| EBS alerts | Real-time | EBS platform |\n",
    "| Vaccination data | Periodic | WHO/AVDA databases |\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 💾 Export Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Save processed data for further analysis:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create output directory\n",
    "output_dir = Path('./output')\n",
    "output_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Export countries\n",
    "countries.to_csv(output_dir / 'africa_countries.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print(\"✅ Exported: africa_countries.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Export regions\n",
    "regions.to_csv(output_dir / 'africa_regions.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print(\"✅ Exported: africa_regions.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Export diseases\n",
    "diseases.to_csv(output_dir / 'africa_priority_diseases.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print(\"✅ Exported: africa_priority_diseases.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\n📁 All files saved to: {output_dir.absolute()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
